# Tailwind Rules
- Use only core Tailwind utility classes
- No arbitrary values in square brackets (e.g., h-[500px])
- No JIT or custom values
- Follow shadcn/ui component styling patterns

# Core Class Examples
## Spacing
- Use: mt-6, p-4, mb-8
- Not: mt-[27px], p-[15px]

## Sizing
- Use: h-64, w-full, text-lg
- Not: h-[600px], w-[42rem], text-[17px]

## Layout
- Use: grid, flex, gap-4
- Not: gap-[10px]

## Typography
- Use: text-sm, text-lg, text-2xl
- Not: text-[22px]

# shadcn/ui Integration
- Import components from @/components/ui
- Use shadcn/ui preset classes
- Maintain consistent component structure
- Follow shadcn/ui theming system

# Component Styling
- Place utility classes before component classes
- Group related utilities together
- Use logical class ordering
- Maintain readability in class lists